                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Short duration buffs are tedious. I'd much rather be mezzing, charming, rooting, nuking, tashing, debuffing, than sitting there waiting for my buffs to refresh so I can buff someone else. I don't want to cast Ferine Avatar, I don't want to cast Ferocity.
<br />

<br />
I'd like to see more raid stackability for enchanters, but I don't think short duration buffs are the way to go.
<br />

<br />
I think a lot of the problems we perceive are content issues where the developers take the easy way out of dealing with enchanters. A lot of raid stackability problems could be eased with content designed to be handled by enchanters.
<br />

<br />
I'm tired of seeing people offtank every mob. I'd like to see mezzable mobs that ignore traditional aggro and go after healers. Mobs that need to be taken care of by casters, rather than the same old "lock aggro, drop mob" routine we see day in day out.
<br />

<br />
Give the raid a reward for bringing an enchanter along, put mobs in that go poof after they've been mezzed for so long, similar to that Sewers trial where the boss steals power from the mobs you mez until they poof.
<br />

<br />
These wouldn't be quick and easy fixes where the devs can affix an asterisk on their patch message, but it would give us something interesting to do on a raid.
<br />

<br />
I'd like to see our Illusions improved, give them a bit of a boost. They're old spells from the old world and they hardly seem effective in today's lands.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-weight: bold"><a href="http://www.bjornstar.com/" target="_blank" class="postlink">Diku Goldenmind</a></span>
