                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Nanyea The Wayward wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"><span style="font-style: italic">An enchanter will rush into a thick crowd of monsters and swirling chaos, and then for a brief instant, bring order mesmerizing and slowing the attacks of the enemy and in some cases confusing the enemy to such a point that they change sides and help the enchanter and his friends.</span>
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I think this sums up why people get addicted to the class.  The ability to fulfill this portion of the role has been steadily nerfed since the release of PoP. 
<br />

<br />
I don't want a bigger nuke as compensation.  I want the chance to be able to walk into a crowd of 4 or 5 mobs and live if I am skilled enough, quick enough.  I want to be able to run to an overpull again, not from it.  Pre-PoP we could do this.
<br />

<br />
You had to be quick to be good.  Now quick isn't enough.  Skill should make a difference.
<br />

<br />
In addition to better ways to loose aggro, we need to be stunned less.  I will gladly pay a lot of AA for something that actually lets me have a better chance of not getting stunned.  Without the constant stuns, I have a chance of doing my job.  If I can get another mez off, the group might be able to live or get away...  If I can get a rune off, I might be able to get another mez off... stun stun stun
<br />

<br />
Yes, this is my dead horse.  I don't care.  There have been times when playing an enchanter gave me an unbelievable adrenaline rush.  The vast majority of those times were pre-PoP or in pre-PoP zones.  I want my rush back.
<br />

<br />
Thank you,
<br />
