                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><span style="font-style: italic">Enchanters are masters of indirect magic and illusions.  They both control and create chaos, either harnessing it for unparalleled power, or reducing it to prevent calamity.  True masters of mind magic, they enhance the spell casting powers of their friends, and confuse and manipulating the minds of their opponents.  As their name suggests, they can also enchant people and things, with powers varing from speeding the swing of a swordarm to bottling the essence of magic itself into a vial.  As force multipliers, they are most at home with allies (either magically coerced or voluntary) to do their dirty work: an enchanter without allies is seriously handicapped.  An Enchanter should have fast reflexes, the ability to keep track of the eb and flow of battle, and must be prepared to know that any mistake may be their last.</span></span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
