                                <td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td><a href="viewtopic.php?p=56815&amp;sid=9b6b7d892414a2918fa1943ba06688f6#56815"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails">Posted: Thu Jul 15, 2004 7:15 am<span class="gen">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; &nbsp;Post subject: Enchanters are all class !</span></td>
                                <td align="right" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><a href="posting.php?mode=quote&amp;p=56815&amp;sid=9b6b7d892414a2918fa1943ba06688f6"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/lang_english/icon_quote.gif" alt="Reply with quote" title="Reply with quote" border="0" /></a>    </td></tr></table></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><span style="font-style: italic">Enchanters are one of the group of classes that focus on the use of magic to the exclusion of physical skills. For all of this group, melee abilities are marginal. 
<br />
Enchanters particular focus of study is pure magic, it's control by the mind and in turn influencing or controlling minds by magic. Enchanters have no particular affinity with Fire, Cold, Poison or Disease related magics. Enchanters trademark is subtlety and they are not apt to harness the raw power of magic but work better by subtle alteration.
<br />
In a group setting an Enchanter provides synergy, increasing other group members performance through magic. Other casters will benefit from an increased mana pool and mana regeneration. Melee classes will benefit from mental focus providing increased attack speed and precision. With this synergistic ability Enchanters function particularly well in groups. In a group an Enchanter can use magic and mental control to slow or blunt the melee ability of enemies, mesmerise or even charm enemies.
<br />
In a solo setting an Enchanter caught unaware by enemies will be easy prey. An enchanters offensive capabilites are rarely sufficient to win a direct encounter. An Enchanter will usually need to render an attacker powerless or turn one attacker against another through charm to avoid death.</span>
<br />

<br />
From this
<br />
Enchanters should have the best Magic Resistance buff and debuff
<br />
Enchanter direct damage should be harnessing of pure mana or mental disruption
<br />
Enchanters should have the best mana regen
<br />
Enchanters should have the best mental powers. Illusion, charm, paccification, mezz, faction adjustment by influencing anothers mind.
<br />

<br />
Enchanters should do less direct damage than the other caster classes who can harness elemental power or raw power.
<br />
Enchanters should not have any magics that affect elemental forces
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
I find it hard to look at the description of Enchanters without reference and comparison. So in a much shorter description:
<br />

<br />
'Pure' Casters:
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Magicians</span> focus on the creation of objects through the use of magics and the manipulation of elemental forces. They have the broadest knowledge of magics. 
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Wizards</span> focus on tapping into the raw power of magic. They can produce the most powerful magical effects through pure and Elemental magics. They sacfiice subtlety and precision for power. They favour force over persuasion
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Necromancers</span> focus on the forces of death and decay which also encompass disease and poison.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
