                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The word enchanter makes me think of someone who uses their mind and illusions to get their way or lure others to their doom.
<br />

<br />
Charm - Beguiles opponents to serve their own end.
<br />
Mesmerization -  Lulls opponents into a dreamlike state.
<br />
Illusion -  Wears a mask of disguise to move more freely in realms that would not abide them.
<br />
Damage - Convinces foes they have been damaged by a spell.  This strong belief makes the foe's mind inflict damage upon their physical being.
<br />
(Best way I can think of enchanter "nukes" making sense within my idea of the class.  It's all about the mind. We aren't really wizards, we just make the opponent think we are.)
<br />
Pacification - Soothes restless spirits enabling the enchanter to pass through their ranks.
<br />
Buffs - Lends mental strength to allies increasing their mental or physical attributes as need.
<br />

<br />
Bunch of rambling.  I'll try to think up a pretty paragraph later.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
